SETUP OVERVIEW

  `SPEECH RESOURCE`

@include.create.resource

@include.create.resource.extra

  `REGION and KEY`

@include.the.azure.speech.service.long

  To select or create an Azure Speech Resource, and automatically store the associated
  KEY and REGION in the SPX configuration datastore:

    spx init

  To manually store your subscription KEY and REGION in the SPX configuration datastore:

    spx config @key --set PUT-YOUR-KEY-HERE
    spx config @region --set PUT-YOUR-REGION-HERE

    For example:

      spx config @key --set 436172626F6E20697320636F6F6C2121
      spx config @region --set westus2

